<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<!DOCTYPE plist PUBLIC "-//Apple//DTD PLIST 1.0//EN" "http://www.apple.com/DTD/PropertyList-1.0.dtd">
<!--
    Minimum-surface entitlements for the app target.

    No `keychain-access-groups` is declared here. When that entitlement
    is absent, iOS restricts the app to its own default access group
    (`<TeamID>.<BundleID>`) — the same isolation as listing the group
    explicitly, but without variable expansion at sign time. Listing
    it explicitly would require `$(AppIdentifierPrefix)` or
    `$(DEVELOPMENT_TEAM)`, either of which causes Xcode to rewrite the
    file during codesign and emit an "Entitlements file was modified
    during the build" error.

    A future extension that needs to share Keychain items with this app
    must add an explicit shared group entitlement to BOTH targets and
    go through a deliberate code-review step — it cannot silently
    inherit the app's credentials. See ADR-0012 §PAT storage.

    Reference: security-review SR-20260419-029.
-->
<plist version="1.0">
<dict/>
</plist>
